Oop, idk if everyone is familiar with the term memephase, probably not! Memephase is also called "RVS" - > https://www.mafiauniverse.com/wiki/RVS Oh, the wiki article mentions "fluffing", that means means Fluff-posting, which is basically just shitchatting and smalltalking with the players, just to have messages in the chat, not necessarily related to the game. Fluff posting can be seen as something unproductive and therefor evil-looking later into the game, as it doesn't contribute to the overall mafia-finding discussion, but early on you usually see it a lot :>
RVS

My version of the story ending after a long discussion, with many confusing messages and many sussed, you decide to point the finger at nexus. It must be him, it has to be, after not helping on d1, after that huge argument with mih. The police promptly remove nexus from the supermarket, but just then, a pair of glowing eyes emerges from the shadows of the Pokemon card section, revealing the spotted cat… that looked murderous? “Zade, do it.” It was cheetah. Cheetah and zade were the criminals. Zade runs forward and slams the supermarket door shut as shiro and mih are making a break for it, trapping them inside… “Oh, how peaceful this started out.” Zade stated. “Everyone was looking at and buying their favourite things. Honestly, I kind of liked it. But a criminal can’t like peace forever. That’s why we decided to cause chaos after learning we were both criminals… and now this supermarket is ours!” Nobody knows what happened, but the police heard hysterical laughter coming from inside. Their fate is still unknown to this day. Perhaps they were killed, perhaps they were enslaved. But the next day, the supermarket was found empty once again, open for more criminals to kill and innocents to test their luck in this death supermarket. (edited)
